race.comment: GAEILGE (3) resumes off a long spell but looks well placed here having his first run for the Freedman yard. He's a Godolphin gelding who has placed in three runs in NSW, going down a neck at Warwick Farm before the break. Fitted with two solid trials leading in, he should take beating, especially post-scratchings with two key dangers coming out. MAHMUDAH (7) resumes for her second campaign having shown a bit of ability last time in. She could be an improver and has claims. WEMBLEY STADIUM (5) hasn't been far away in two runs to date and can figure while BLUEY MERCHANT (2) has been solid at the jumpouts and can run well on debut.
